00:55:42.080 --> 00:55:43.510
And are those better modes of--

00:55:43.510 --> 00:55:45.926
CELESTE HEADLEE: Yes, video
conferences are totally legit.

00:55:45.926 --> 00:55:48.140
Phone conversation
is totally legit.

00:55:48.140 --> 00:55:50.140
And now, one of the things
that email does well,

00:55:50.140 --> 00:55:52.306
remember I said that it
only does a few things well.

00:55:52.306 --> 00:55:54.490
One of them is that time
lapse, handling time lapse.

00:55:54.490 --> 00:55:57.120
It also, you know, it's one
of the best ways to, you know,

00:55:57.120 --> 00:55:59.200
send an attachment.

00:55:59.200 --> 00:56:02.107
It's also the best way to recap
a meeting or a phone call.

00:56:02.107 --> 00:56:03.565
So for example, if
I have something

00:56:03.565 --> 00:56:05.560
where I need a
nuance, or we need

00:56:05.560 --> 00:56:08.680
to sort of hash something out,
I will always do that by phone.

00:56:08.680 --> 00:56:10.282
And I make people
do it by phone.

00:56:10.282 --> 00:56:11.740
Like, they'll try
to do it in email

00:56:11.740 --> 00:56:13.360
and I'll say, I don't think
this is the kind of thing we're

00:56:13.360 --> 00:56:14.830
going to be able to
handle over email,

00:56:14.830 --> 00:56:16.060
give me a time when
you have five or 10

00:56:16.060 --> 00:56:17.230
minutes on the phone, right.

00:56:17.230 --> 00:56:18.813
And then I will call
him on the phone.

00:56:18.813 --> 00:56:21.160
And then when the phone
conversation is done,

00:56:21.160 --> 00:56:24.610
