saying, here's what I heard.

00:56:24.610 --> 00:56:26.020
This is what we talked about.

00:56:26.020 --> 00:56:27.820
Is this what you heard also?

00:56:27.820 --> 00:56:31.300
That's where you can use email
really, really productively.

00:56:31.300 --> 00:56:33.400
But to have any
kind of discussion

00:56:33.400 --> 00:56:35.380
over email, every
bit of research

00:56:35.380 --> 00:56:38.020
that we have shows the
email makes it worse.

00:56:38.020 --> 00:56:40.780
It's It's a productivity killer.

00:56:40.780 --> 00:56:42.929
It's an innovation killer.

00:56:42.929 --> 00:56:44.470
It's much better to
have it by phone.

00:56:44.470 --> 00:56:46.780
Now, a video
conference, absolutely.

00:56:46.780 --> 00:56:48.670
Your phone call, absolutely.

00:56:48.670 --> 00:56:50.315
Absolutely.

00:56:50.315 --> 00:56:51.940
Remember, you know,
there's three parts

00:56:51.940 --> 00:56:55.060
to successful
communication, right.

00:56:55.060 --> 00:56:57.790
There's the words that you use,
the vocabulary, what they mean.

00:56:57.790 --> 00:56:59.180
Then there's your body language.

00:56:59.180 --> 00:57:00.710
And then there's
your tone of voice.

00:57:00.710 --> 00:57:03.920
So there's a reason why we
make jokes about sarcasm font,

00:57:03.920 --> 00:57:04.420
right.

00:57:04.420 --> 00:57:07.777
It's because me, if I
say (tentative) maybe

00:57:07.777 --> 00:57:10.360
that's really different me going
(cheerful affirmative) maybe,

00:57:10.360 --> 00:57:10.859
right.

00:57:10.859 --> 00:57:13.000
One of them means no.

00:57:13.000 --> 00:57:16.480
And that is not translated
through your printed word.

00:57:16.480 --> 00:57:19.270
This is why we have
Damn You Auto Correct!

00:57:19.270 --> 00:57:21.580
This is why we have all those
things making fun of how

00:57:21.580 --> 00:57:25.150
bad texting communication is.

00:57:25.150 --> 00:57:27.520
When you are just
emailing or texting,

00:57:27.520 --> 00:57:30.250
you're removing
2/3 of the meaning

00:57:30.250 --> 00:57:31.780
from what it is
that you're saying.

00:57:31.780 --> 00:57:34.660
So it's not at all surprising
that miscommunications

00:57:34.660 --> 00:57:35.650
happen all the time.

